title: For Sale/Trade:  **true Tromix Saiga 12 heavily modified.  quad rail, red jacket muzzle brake, push button folding stock, welded galil charging handle
postcontent:
*disclaimer:  for those of you who think every gun is created equal or that every gun should only be $300, please don't contact me.  
I told Tony I'd never get rid of it but just seeing what else is out there.  Build list as follows:

> Tromix converted absolutely flawless Saiga 12 gauge shotgun.  Tony opens up the gas ports, moves forward the fire control group, welds on his Tromix trigger guard and grip hanger, welds on a receiver back plate to accept high end stocks and remachines tang to correct angle, welds up old holes in receiver etc.
>SRTrigger (short reset trigger)
> bolt hold open lever
> aluminum tri/quad rail.  Has removable top rail with peep hole to see factory iron sights
> far rear side mount rail for full upper rail to mount optics, red dot, etc and still have see through factory irons
> stubby foregrip with storage
> Red Jacket Firearms Mojo muzzle brake (one of the best for recoil reduction and muzzle rise)
> Carolina Shooter Supply aluminum push button folding stock adapter
> Carolina Shooter Supply raptor aluminum stock with height adjustable cheek rest and cheek pad, with added 1" recoil pad
> hk style removable iron sights, with 4 size holes (not pictured on this listing, but can send pics with them installed)
> Hogue and factory grips
> bonus extra tri rail I have laying around
> I'll have to add it up but I think there's a total of 11+ magazines.  Five or more 5 rd mags, At least six 10 rd mags and one 20 rd drum
> has optional welded on galil style charging handle, I had Tony weld this on at an angle as to not scrape your hand like a meat slicer (only Tromix like this to my knowledge)
> Carolina Shooter Supply reliability kit with upgraded gas puck and 6 position gas plug.  With a simple twist of this plug you can reliably shoot anything..I mean ANYTHING.  It shoots low brass, high brass, birdshot, buckshot, slugs, WHATEVER!!! It shoots Winchester universal all day, EPIC fun and cheaper than Hell.

I'm sure I'm missing something but this is by far the most fun and one of the coolest looking firearm made, if I might be so bold as to state.  This thing is built to perform.  It can empty the 20 rd drum in less than 3 seconds.  THE BUILD LIST FOR A SIMILAR TROMIX Saiga 12 is 2-3 YEARS.

As far as price goes, I'm open to offers from smart, non Lowballing, American loving individuals, who are preferably republican.  I know there's somebody out there who knows what this is and actual can manage his money and pay for what they want.  Lowball cash offers will be totally ignored, if you want a bone stock Saiga then buy one.  There's not one Tromix under $1995 that I'm aware of.  Look it up, the only true Tromix on AL I saw was in Arkansas and he's asking $2450.  If your offer isn't over 2 grand don't bother contacting me.  I'm not hurting for cash, I don't need to get rid of it by any means.  I'm testing the cash and trade market.  Period. 

As far as trades go, I'm VERY picky on my guns.  I recently traded all my dead weight guns and have acquired most of the guns I wanted.  I don't want ANY shotguns besides a new black ksg.  I don't want ANY rifles at all besides maybe a ps90, unless you're wanting over $1300 for it on trade.  Period end of story.

If you're out of state, forget it.  emails only responded to when they're worth a crap.  Tons of detailed pics available on request.  
**Anybody who wants to text or email and argue over prices and what gun is better or worth more than others can kick rocks.  I have an opinion, same as everybody.  Sometimes they differ, it's as simple as that.

This was a long post so I don't have to say these same things 100 times to everybody that contacts me.

Daniel Defense’s new caliber option, the 300 Blackout, was originally designed to give the shooter a 30 caliber projectile which could be fired out of the AR platform without an increase in magazine size while still utilizing a standard bolt. The 300 Blackout is 7.62x35mm which gives the shooter similar ballistic qualities as the .308 and the 7.62x39mm, the AK round, without having to give up the light weight 5.56mm/AR platform. All of today's standard 45 colt loads are very anemic. Often featuring a 250 gr. Bullet at around 700 fps.

Jacketed Hollow Point at around 1,100fps. We wanted loads that were substantially more powerful than today's weenie loads, but that could be fired in ANY 45 colt firearm.

Both of these 45 colt loads are designed to be a heavy loading, yet be within standard (SAAMI) pressure. As such, both of these 45 colt loads are safe and recommended to be used IN ANY post-war 45 colt that is in normal working condition. ANY post-war means ANY post-war, so please take my word for it without phoning or emailing me "just to make sure". I love hearing from and appreciate customers, I really do, but there is no sense using up your or my time answering questions that have already been answered.

These loads are indeed heavy 45 colt loadings. You can fire them in any post-war firearm that is in normal working condition chambered for 45 colt without reservation.
